ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Manic/Hypomanic Syndrome present during the past month?
Notes: 1 = No; 5 = Yes; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped

ElementDescription: Total number of Manic Syndromes
Notes: Number of manic episodes; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped; 99 = Greater than 93

ElementDescription: Age of onset of first Manic Syndrome
Notes: Onset age in years; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped. Ages reflect that SCID disorders were assessed for the last 3 years or, if no episode in the last 3 years, time since last interview.

ElementDescription: Age of recency of last Manic Syndrome
Notes: Age of recency in years; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped. Ages reflect that SCID disorders were assessed for the last 3 years or, if no episode in the last 3 years, time since last interview.

ElementDescription: If Chronology was not filled out for ANY SCID Disorders (due to skipping out of ALL sections), circle 1 and do not fill out rest of form. Otherwise, circle 5 and continue, coding 98 for any individual sections that were skipped.
Notes: 1 = Skip out of form; 5 = Continue; 9 = Missing

ElementDescription: Major Depressive Syndrome (MDS) present during the past month?
Notes: 1 = No; 5 = Yes; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped

ElementDescription: Last time Major Depressive Syndrome (MDS) symptoms were present (in months)
Notes: Number in months; 994=Refused to Answer; 995=Don''t Know; 996=Missing; 997=Accidentally Skipped; 998=Purposely Skipped; 999 = Greater than 993

ElementDescription: Age of recency of Major Depressive Syndrome (MDS) symptoms
Notes: Age in years; 94=Refused to Answer; 95=Don''t Know; 96=Missing; 97=Accidentally Skipped; 98=Purposely Skipped. Ages reflect that SCID disorders were assessed for the last 3 years or, if no episode in the last 3 years, time since last interview.

ElementDescription: Total number of Major Depressive Syndrome (MDS) episodes

ElementDescription: Age of onset of first Major Depressive Syndrome (MDS)
